               <head>Collectanea of St Mary's Abbey, York</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem class="#monastica" n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_39-item1">
                     <locus>(fol. 1)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14306">Regula S. Benedicti</title>
                     <rubric>Regula patris eximii Benedicti</rubric>
                     <note>With prologue and list of chapters, and drawings of an abbot and novice: imperfect at end, wanting all after 'subditum &amp; magis' in ch. 60. A form of admission for a novice 'ad monasterium sancte Marie Eboracensis' in the time of Simon de Warwick (abbot 1258–96) is at fol. 1.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="#monastica" n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_39-item2">
                     <locus>(fol. 32)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14301">Regula S. Augustini ad seruos Dei</title>
                     <rubric>Regula sancti Augustini de uita clericorum</rubric>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="#monastica" n="3" xml:id="MS_Bodl_39-item3">
                     <locus>(fol. 38)</locus>
                     <title key="work_14717" type="desc">Statutes of Benedictine Chapters</title>
                     <note>Including: (fol. 38) the papal constitutions appointed in 1268 to be written after the monastic rule: (fol. 46v) Statutes of Ottobonus, made at London in 1268: (fol. 52v) Statutes of a Chapter of the province of Canterbury, 1275: (fol. 67v) Treatise on the obedientiaries and rites of a certain monastery, evidently St. Mary's abbey, see fol. 91v: imperfect, ending with the rubric of a section 'De ingressu nouiciorum ...'</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 92)</locus>
                     <author key="person_3205">Stephen of Whitby</author>
                     <title key="work_6600">‘De fundacione abbatie sancte Marie Virginis Eboracensis’</title>
                     <note>With a list of abbots and brief annals to 1267, with drawings.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 101)</locus>
                     <author key="person_299286120">Thurstan, archbishop of York</author>
                     <title key="work_6599">Epistola de egressu monachorum Fontanensium</title>
                     <note>A copy of a letter from Thurstan, archbp. of York, describing the foundation of St. Mary's abbey at Fountains by a colony from the York house in 1132: but foll. 101–9, 113–114 are later copies of about 1400, substituted: foll. 114v-115v are blank.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 116)</locus>
                     <title key="work_10192" type="desc">Annals of St Mary's Abbey, York, 1258–1326</title>
                     <note>Detailed annals of the abbey, with drawings, in perturbed order and with erasures and substituted leaves: at 1284 come in (foll. 135–149) Statutes of Benedictine Chapters of the province of York, 1222–1333; (foll. 150–161) lists of priors or wardens of cells of the abbey. The hands seems to change and be contemporary from about 1312: later substituted leaves are foll. 135, 149, 171, 174. At fol. 205v a late 14th cent. hand has added 'Modus &amp; forma eligendi abbatem'. At fol. 116 is a list of the monks in 1258.</note>
                  </msItem>
